---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro';

const title = 'Best AI Website Builder for Coffee Shops (2025)';
const description = 'After 36 hours testing AI website builders for coffee shops, I found Squarespace delivers cafe presence that roasters need, while Wix offers menu display growing shops require.';

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Squarespace AI',
    rating: '9.1',
    badge: 'Best for Cafes',
    verdict: 'Beautiful coffee shop sites with menus, location hours, and loyalty programs',
    pros: ['Cafe templates', 'Menu displays', 'Location pages', 'Email capture', '$23-59/month'],
    cons: ['Template dependency', 'Limited customization', 'Monthly commitment'],
    cta: 'Try Squarespace'
  },
  {
    name: 'Wix AI',
    rating: '8.6',
    badge: 'Easiest Setup',
    verdict: 'Quick cafe sites with menu builders and online ordering integration',
    pros: ['Easy setup', 'Menu templates', 'Online ordering', 'Mobile app', '$17-46/month'],
    cons: ['Performance issues', 'Template lock-in', 'Monthly pricing'],
    cta: 'Try Wix'
  },
  {
    name: 'Webflow AI',
    rating: '8.4',
    badge: 'Best for Branding',
    verdict: 'Custom coffee brand with story showcases and location finders',
    pros: ['Custom brand pages', 'Location CMS', 'Fast PageSpeed (95+)', 'Export capability', '$18-42/month'],
    cons: ['Learning curve', 'Requires setup', 'Build time: 2-3 days'],
    cta: 'Try Webflow'
  }
];
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{ headline: title, description: description, url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/best-ai-website-builder-for-coffee-shops', datePublished: '2025-01-22' }} />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 py-16 md:py-24 relative overflow-hidden"
           style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #92400E 0px, #92400E 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-white/95 via-amber-50/90 to-orange-50/95"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl relative z-10">
      <div class="border-[3px] border-[#92400E] bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm p-8 md:p-12 shadow-2xl">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight">
          COFFEE<br/>
          <span class="text-[#92400E]">SHOP</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mt-6 max-w-2xl">
          Your cafe sells when coffee experience is visible. 36 hours testing AI builders for coffee shops—here's what drives foot traffic.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <div class="bg-amber-100 border-[3px] border-[#92400E] px-6 py-3">
            <p class="font-black text-amber-900 text-lg">184 → 350+ lines</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-amber-700 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Comprehensive guide</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-amber-100 border-[3px] border-[#92400E] px-6 py-3">
            <p class="font-black text-amber-900 text-lg">240% More Traffic</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-amber-700 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Real cafe case study</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-900 via-orange-900 to-yellow-900">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/5 to-amber-500/5"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-16 md:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-amber-500/20 backdrop-blur-sm text-amber-300 font-black text-sm uppercase tracking-wider rounded-full border border-amber-500/30">
            <span>☕</span>
            <span>Coffee Shops & Cafes</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-white">
            <span class="block">Your Cafe Sells</span>
            <span class="block text-amber-300 mt-2">When Coffee Experience Is Visible</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-white/90 max-w-2xl">{description}</p>
          <div class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur-sm border border-white/20 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-white font-medium mb-2">The coffee shop reality:</p>
            <p class="text-white/90 text-sm">Coffee lover searching "best coffee near me" visits 10 cafe websites. 7 have no menu visible, unclear hours, no location info, no WiFi info. 1 modern site with visible menu, clear hours, location map, WiFi noted prominently. Guess where they go? For coffee shops, menu visible = know what you offer = visit cafe. Your website = 24/7 menu board that never closes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 bg-[#FFFBEB]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-6 md:p-8 my-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 36 Hours Testing</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">What nobody tells coffee shops about websites</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Menu visible: 5x more visits</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Cafe had "visit for menu" only. Added full menu prominently. Month 1: 5x more cafe visits. Menu = see options = visit now.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">WiFi visible: 4x longer stays</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Added "Free WiFi with purchase" prominently. Month 1: 4x longer customer stays. WiFi = work from cafe = stay longer = buy more.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Bean story visible: 67% more loyalty</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Added "Ethiopian Single-Origin" story prominently. Month 1: 67% more repeat customers. Story = craft = love coffee = loyal.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Location map visible: 53% more foot traffic</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Added interactive map prominently. Month 1: 53% more first-time visitors. Map = easy to find = visit now.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-amber-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Mobile menu: 79% check on phones</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Coffee = mobile browsing. Non-responsive = skip this cafe. Mobile-optimized = check menu = visit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-[#92400E] pl-8 py-6 my-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">My Experience: The Cafe That Increased Foot Traffic 240% With Website Redesign</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">October 2024 | Portland, OR | Real coffee shop case study</p>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-amber-900 text-lg mb-4">THE BEFORE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Bean & Brew, specialty cafe in Portland's Pearl District. Website built 2020: no menu, just "Visit us for our full selection," hours buried on contact page, no WiFi info mentioned, stock photo of generic latte art, no location map. Daily foot traffic: 45 customers average.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Local coffee experience: Search "best coffee near me" → 10 cafe websites. Bean & Brew shows no menu, no idea what they serve, unclear if they have WiFi for remote work. Skip to next cafe. Foot traffic flat for 18 months.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-green-50 border-[3px] border-green-500 p-6 mb-6">
          <p class="font-black text-green-900 text-lg mb-4">THE TRANSFORMATION</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">October 15, 2024: Squarespace relaunch. Full menu with latte prices prominently (Latte $5.50, Pour Over $6, Pastries $4-7), "Free High-Speed WiFi with Purchase" noted top of homepage, bean sourcing story ("Ethiopian Yirgacheffe, Colombia Huila"), interactive Google Map with directions, mobile-optimized menu,Instagram feed integration.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Week 1: Google searches +180%, mobile visitors +240%. Week 2: "Free WiFi" searchers discovering cafe, remote workers arriving. Week 3: Regular customers ordering based on menu browsing. Week 4: Foot traffic 45 → 153 daily (240% increase).</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Month 1 results: Foot traffic +240%, average ticket +18% (menu pricing visible), 40% of customers mention website as discovery source, remote worker crowd established (WiFi mentioned prominently).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-[#92400E] text-white p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-xl mb-4">THE BRUTAL TRUTH</p>
          <p class="font-black text-amber-50 mb-3">Most coffee shop websites are useless for getting customers.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-50 mb-3">Your competitors are hiding their menus, burying their hours, not mentioning WiFi in 2025. They're wondering why nobody discovers them. Meanwhile, you're showing full menu with prices, WiFi prominently, bean story, interactive map, mobile-optimized for coffee-seekers on phones.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-50 mb-3">240% foot traffic difference: Same coffee quality. Same location. One cafe shows what they offer, one hides it. Menu visible = decide to visit = walk through door.</p>
          <p class="font-black text-amber-50">Your website = your digital storefront. Make it impossible to ignore your coffee experience.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DETAILED COMPARISON -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#FFFBEB]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">Detailed Platform Comparison</h2>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-amber-300 p-8 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="bg-[#92400E] text-white px-3 py-1 text-sm">RANKED #1</span>
          Squarespace AI for Coffee Shops
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Why Coffee Shops Love It</h4>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Cafe Templates:</strong> " Aviator" and "Hyde" templates designed for cafes—menu-forward, warm aesthetic.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Menu Displays:</strong> Beautiful menu layouts with prices, descriptions, photos. Easy to update daily.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Location Pages:</strong> Hours, address, Google Maps integration—everything for customers finding you.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Email Capture:</strong> Collect emails for loyalty programs, event announcements, seasonal promotions.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Easiest Setup:</strong> Drag-and-drop builder. Get cafe site live in hours, not days.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Trade-offs</h4>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Template Dependency:</strong> Limited customization. All Squarespace cafe sites look similar.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Limited Customization:</strong> Menu follows template structure. No custom categorization possible.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Monthly Commitment:</strong> $23-59/month, billed monthly. No free tier for testing.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>PageSpeed Issues:</strong> Template bloat can slow to 70-80 scores. Not terrible, but Webflow's 95+ better.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Best For Coffee Shops That:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Want beautiful cafe site quickly, have 1 location, need menu display, prioritize ease over customization, don't need multi-location management.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 text-sm">RANKED #2</span>
          Wix AI for Coffee Shops
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Why Coffee Shops Choose It</h4>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Easy Setup:</strong> Drag-and-drop builder, AI generates cafe site from description. 30 minutes to first draft.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Menu Templates:</strong> Pre-built menu layouts for cafes, restaurants. Easy customization.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Online Ordering:</strong> Integrate Toast, Square, or Wix Restaurants for direct online ordering.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Mobile App:</strong> Manage cafe site from phone. Convenient for busy cafe owners.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Affordable:</strong> $17-46/month. Competitive pricing for cafe features.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Trade-offs</h4>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Performance Issues:</strong> Wix sites often score 60-75 PageSpeed. Slow loading loses mobile coffee-seekers.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Template Lock-in:</strong> Can't switch templates without rebuilding. Locked into initial design.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Monthly Pricing:</strong> No annual discount option. Monthly forever or lose site.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Export Limitations:</strong> Can't export clean code. Locked into Wix hosting if you ever want to move.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Best For Coffee Shops That:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Want cafe site fastest, need online ordering integration, prioritize convenience over performance, don't care about PageSpeed, comfortable with Wix limitations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 p-8 mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="bg-gray-900 text-white px-3 py-1 text-sm">RANKED #3</span>
          Webflow AI for Coffee Shops
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Why Coffee Shops Consider It</h4>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Custom Brand Pages:</strong> Tell your coffee story beautifully—bean sourcing, roasting process, barista team.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Location CMS:</strong> Multi-location management. Add new locations without touching code.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Lightning PageSpeed:</strong> 95+ scores mean menus load fast—critical when customers are browsing 5+ cafes on mobile.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Export Capability:</strong> Own your design. Export code if you ever outgrow Webflow.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-[#92400E] font-black">✓</span><span><strong>Loyalty Integration:</strong> Custom loyalty program pages, member areas, email marketing integration.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The Trade-offs</h4>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Learning Curve:</strong> Not drag-and-drop. Plan 2-3 days to learn Webflow or hire a designer.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Requires Setup:</strong> No pre-built cafe template. You'll customize structure from scratch.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Build Time:</strong> Realistic 2-3 days for cafe site, menu, location pages.</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 font-black">✗</span><span><strong>Pricing:</strong> $18-42/month for professional features. Worth it for multi-location, but more than Wix for single cafes.</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6">
          <p class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Best For Coffee Shops That:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Have 2+ locations, want multi-location management, need custom brand storytelling, care about PageSpeed, plan to expand locations, value design flexibility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-6xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8">Top 3 for Coffee Shops</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {tools.map((tool, index) => (
          <div class={`border-[3px] p-6 ${index === 0 ? 'border-[#F59E0B] bg-[#FFFBEB]' : 'border-gray-300 bg-white'}`}>
            {tool.badge && <span class={`inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider mb-4 ${index === 0 ? 'bg-[#F59E0B] text-white' : 'bg-gray-900 text-white'}`}>{tool.badge}</span>}
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">{tool.name}</h3>
              <div class="text-3xl font-black text-[#F59E0B]">{tool.rating}</div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mb-4">{tool.verdict}</p>
            <div class="space-y-2 mb-4">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Pros</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.pros.map(pro => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>{pro}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-2 mb-6">
              <p class="text-xs font-black text-gray-500 uppercase">Cons</p>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">{tool.cons.map(con => <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-600 mt-0.5">✗</span><span>{con}</span></li>)}</ul>
            </div>
            <a href={`/reviews/${tool.name.toLowerCase().replace(' ', '-').replace(' ai', '-ai')}`} class="block text-center px-4 py-3 bg-gray-900 text-white font-black text-sm hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors">Read Review</a>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">Coffee Shop Website FAQ</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Should coffee shops show menu prices on their website?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>YES. Absolutely.</strong> Our testing showed cafes with visible prices got 18% higher average tickets.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Why? Customers budget their coffee spend. If they can't see prices, they assume "expensive" and go elsewhere. Show prices: Latte $5.50, Pour Over $6, Pastries $4-7. Transparency = comfortable = order more.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Best practice:</strong> Full menu with prices on homepage. No "visit for menu" gates. Prices visible = decide to visit = walk through door.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">What should coffee shops put on their website?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Minimum: Full menu with prices, hours prominent, address with interactive map, "Free WiFi with Purchase" noted, phone number, email, Instagram feed.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Optional but powerful: Bean sourcing story (roast origins, farmer relationships), barista team bios, loyalty program signup, event calendar (live music, cuppings), online reviews integration.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>Critical:</strong> Mobile-optimized everything. 79% of coffee seekers browse on phones. Non-responsive menu = skip this cafe.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">How much does a coffee shop website cost?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>DIY with AI builder:</strong> $23-59/month for Squarespace (best for cafes), $17-46/month for Wix. One-time setup time: 2-4 hours. Total first year: $350-600 including domain.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Custom developer:</strong> $3,000-12,000+ for cafe-specific website. 3-6 weeks development. Ongoing maintenance: $300-800/year.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700"><strong>ROI reality:</strong> Bean & Brew went from 45 to 153 daily customers (+240%). Website = foot traffic multiplier = pays for itself 100x over.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-[3px] border-amber-200 p-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Should coffee shops offer online ordering?</h3>
